						               													<description>Now there's a new way for readers to discuss their passions, with the release of The Art of Conversation: Literary Edition, a new game from the makers of The Art of Conversation.&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;Following the success of their original games, creators Louise Howland and Keith Lamb have adapted the concept to offer new angles and avenues to think, and talk, about books.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#151;&amp;#143; TAOC&amp;reg; comes with 300 starter questions plus a 32-page guidebook that includes informative and comprehensive endnotes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#151;&amp;#143; Carefully developed and researched by the creators, with the assistance of well-respected literature teacher Leila Bryant, there&amp;rsquo;s plenty of scope to come up with your own questions. Like all TAOC editions, it&amp;rsquo;s not a quiz &amp;ndash; it&amp;rsquo;s not about who knows the most. It&amp;rsquo;s a communication tool that draws on your own experiences, thoughts and reactions to facilitate fascinating discussions.&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#151;&amp;#143; Even reluctant readers will be drawn in! Readers of all stages and ages will find themselves being educated, all in the name of fun.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#151;&amp;#143; Ideal for book clubs, but can also be adapted to friends, family, workmates, students or even solitary readers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#226;&amp;#151;&amp;#143; Covers all genres &amp;ndash; fiction, poetry, drama, biography, autobiography, science fiction, fantasy, crime, romance, historical writing - essentially, the whole bookshop!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
